1 sheet ([1] p.) : ill.(port.)
s.n., [London : 1642]
"An engraved portrait, by Hollar, of Thomas Killigrew the elder, with satirical verses." -- Thomason catalogue. Verse attributed to Thomas Killigrew by Wing. Title from first line of text. Verse - "Foole that I was, who has so faire a state,". Imprint from Wing. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
